# This file describes patterns of files and folders that should be excluded   #
# from git status and git add. Specifically, we ignore files associated with  #
# the binary version of the package (the build/) and binary files, which we   #
# identify with .o extensions. We also ignore data (HDF5) files generated by  #
# the library. We also ignore files generated by LaTeX.                       #
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------## We ignore the build folder created by
# the library.
build/

# We ignore the stats generated by gitstats.
stats/

# We ignore binary files (which must have a .o) extension.
*.o
*.pdf

# We ignore the HDF5 files generated by the library.
*.hdf5
*.hdf5-*

# We ignore other data files
*.dat
*.xmf*
tests/dummy_data
*.txt
simulations/develUtilities

# -- Source: https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/master/TeX.gitignore
